('BET302', 'Biomedical Electronics ', 'This course is an introduction to the fundamentals of analog electronics with an emphasis on biomedical applications. Students will be introduced to solid state devices including diodes, transistors, operational amplifiers, oscillators, and mixers and their use in power supplies, amplifiers and active filters.', 4.00, 'E', 0.00, 0),
